-- VTB to Overhaul Stalin-Era Dinamo Stadium to Help Russia's World Cup Bid
-- Ilya Khrennikov
-- 2010-06-29T05:19:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/vtb-to-overhaul-stalin-era-dinamo-stadium-to-help-russia-s-world-cup-bid.html

          
          
             VTB Group, Russia’s second-largest
bank, plans a $1.4 billion overhaul of the Stalin-era Dinamo
soccer stadium in Moscow to help the country’s bid to host the
2018 World Cup.  
 Dutch architect Erick Van Egeraat will design the
reconstruction of the stadium, which was built in 1928, state-
run VTB said on its website. The project is due to be completed
by 2016, VTB said.  
